    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-02T11:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-02T11:40:00-05:00" n="448"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/978.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-02T12:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1913—Noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Government is impatient of my insistence upon decent elections, and has
                    arrested three principal orators of the opposition. The nightly demonstrations
                    give color of right to the Government’s course, and the opposition probably
                    hopes for American intervention. Placards are posted about the city quoting my
                    written promises to secure constitutional remedies. I urge sending the
                    additional vessel immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
